net.hudup.core.data.ctx

Class ContextList

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.ctx.ContextList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class ContextList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Cloneable
    This class represents a list of context that a user rates on an item. Context is additional information related to user rating, for example, place that user makes a rating, companion indicating the persons with whom user makes a rating such as alone, friends, girlfriend/boyfriend, family, co-workers. Context is represented by Context class. As a convention, this class is called context list, which provides utility methods to process (add, set, remove, etc.) a list of contexts. This class has a built-in variable list that is the List of Context.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen

      • canInferFrom

        public boolean canInferFrom(Context context)
        Given the specified context, this method returns true if all contexts inside this list can be inferred from such specified context. Otherwise, this method returns false. Please see Context.canInferFrom(Context) for more details about the concept "can be inferred from"
        Parameters:
        context - The specified context.
        Returns:
        whether this context list is inferred by the specified context

      • canInferFrom

        public boolean canInferFrom(ContextList contexts)
        Given the specified context list, this method returns true if all contexts inside this list can be inferred from such specified context list. Otherwise, this method returns false. Of course this methods calls canInferFrom(Context) method. Please see Context.canInferFrom(Context) for more details about the concept "can be inferred from"
